*fclose*

(PHP 4, PHP 5, PHP 7, PHP 8)

fclose â€” Closes an open file pointer

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  fclose(resource $stream): bool~

The file pointed to by {stream} is closed.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{stream}

  The file pointer must be valid, and must point to a file successfully opened
  by |fopen| or |fsockopen|.

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

Returns true on success or false on failure.

===============================================================================
[ Examples ]

Example #1 A simple fclose() example

<?php >

  $handle = fopen('somefile.txt', 'r');

  fclose($handle);

<?>

===============================================================================
